    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-11-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <head>A.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jenkins</persName> to
                            Mr. <persName type="to">Shepard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 1,
                            1878</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to hand you the original order which was
                        sent to my agent at Chung Ching, in Chinese, with a copy of it in English.
                        It is from Lee, the magistrate of Chung Ching. It explains itself. I have to
                        request that you will forward a copy of it to his excellency the minister at
                        Peking, and have most respectfully to ask that steps be taken as early as
                        possible to prevent further heavy loss. I shall forward, as soon as
                        received, particulars of a claim for loss of market, interest, &amp;c.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. ANDREW JENKINS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
